@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}


<div class="privacy-ctn">
    <h1 class="privacy-heading">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <p class="indented">Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how Library collects, uses, and protects the personal information you provide when using our library application and services.</p>
    <div class="chapter-ctn">
        <h4>1. Information We Collect</h4>
        <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
        <ul>
            1. Personal Information:
            <li>Name</li>
            <li>Email address</li>
            <li>User role (e.g., Admin, Member)</li>
            <li>Account credentials (username and password)</li>
            2. Usage Data:
            <li>Pages or features you access</li>
            <li>Time and date of your interactions</li>
            <li>IP address or device information (for security purposes)</li>
            3. Favorites or Preferences:
            <li>Books you mark as favorites</li>
            <li>Genres you engage with frequently</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter-ctn">
        <h4>2. How We Use Your Information</h4>
        <p>We use your information for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To provide and manage library services, including borrowing and returning books.</li>
            <li>To manage user roles (e.g., Admin, Member) for authorization and access control.</li>
            <li>To improve user experience by analyzing usage trends.</li>
            <li>To send notifications about updates, new books, or policy changes (if you opt in).</li>
            <li>To ensure the security of our platform and detect unauthorized access.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter-ctn">
        <h4>3. How We Protect Your Information</h4>
        <p>We take the protection of your information seriously. Our measures include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Secure storage of data using encryption.</li>
            <li>Regular monitoring for potential security vulnerabilities.</li>
            <li>Restricting access to personal data to authorized personnel only.</li>
            <li>Implementing role-based access to sensitive features (e.g., Admin-only functions).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter-ctn">
        <h4>4. Sharing Your Information</h4>
        <p>We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>With service providers who assist in platform maintenance or analytics.</li>
            <li>To comply with legal obligations or respond to lawful requests.</li>
            <li>To protect the rights, property, or safety of Library, our users, or others.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter-ctn">
        <h4>5. Your Rights</h4>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access, update, or delete your personal information.</li>
            <li>Opt-out of non-essential communications, such as promotional emails.</li>
            <li>Request clarification on how your data is used.</li>
            To exercise your rights, contact us at
            <a class="navigation-link contact-link" asp-area="" asp-page="/ContactPage">Contact</a>.
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter-ctn">
        <h4>6. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h4>
        <p>Our platform may use cookies to enhance your experience by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Remembering your login session.</li>
            <li>Analyzing usage patterns to improve functionality.</li>
            You can control cookie preferences through your browser settings.
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter-ctn">
        <h4>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h4>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with the updated "Effective Date."</p>
    </div>
</div>
